article.description: C.J. Keyser had a career-high 23 points as NC Central extended its home win streak to seven games, defeating South Carolina State 73-56 on Saturday.
article.headline: Keyser scores 23 to carry NC Central over SC State 73-56
article.linkText: Keyser scores 23 to carry NC Central over SC State 73-56
article.story: DURHAM, N.C. -- C.J. Keyser had a career-high 23 points as NC Central extended its home win streak to seven games, defeating South Carolina State 73-56 on Saturday. Keyser made 9 of 12 shots. Jibri Blount had 10 points for NC Central (9-12, 5-2 Mid-Eastern Conference). Jordan Perkins added seven assists. Tashombe Riley had 13 points for the Bulldogs (9-11, 4-4). Tariq Simmons added 12 points. NC Central plays Norfolk State at home on Monday. South Carolina State matches up against NC A&T on the road on Monday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
